quran[27]{c,v,t,f}:
  68,34,"Verily, for the Muttaqûn (the pious - See V.2:2) are Gardens of delight (Paradise) with their Lord."
  68,35,"Shall We then treat the Muslims (believers of Islamic Monotheism, doers of righteous deeds) like the Mujrimûn (criminals, polytheists and disbelievers, etc.)?"
  68,36,"What is the matter with you? How judge you?"
  69,31,"Then throw him in the blazing Fire."
  69,32,""
  69,33,"Verily, he used not to believe in Allâh, the Most Great,"
  70,25,"For the beggar who asks, and for the unlucky who has lost his property and wealth, (and his means of living has been straitened)."
  70,26,"And those who believe in the Day of Recompense."
  70,27,"And those who fear the torment of their Lord."
  71,22,""
  71,23,""
  71,24,""
  72,19,"And when the slave of Allâh (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) stood up invoking Him (his Lord - Allâh) in prayer they (the jinn) just made round him a dense crowd as if sticking one over the other (in order to listen to the Prophet’s recitation)."
  72,20,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  72,21,"Say: "
  73,13,"And a food that chokes, and a painful torment."
  73,14,"On the Day when the earth and the mountains will be in violent shake, and the mountains will be a heap of sand poured out."
  73,15,"Verily, We have sent to you (O men) a Messenger (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) to be a witness over you, as We did send a Messenger [Mûsâ (Moses)] to Fir‘aun (Pharaoh).{1}",footnotes:1:[{73:15} See the footnotes of {2:252}.]
  74,10,"Far from easy for the disbelievers."
  74,11,"Leave Me Alone (to deal) with whom I created lonely (without any wealth or children etc, i.e. Al-Walîd bin Al-Mughîrah Al-Makhzûmî)!"
  74,12,"And then granted him resources in abundance."
  75,7,"So, when the sight shall be dazed."
  75,8,"And the moon will be eclipsed."
  75,9,"And the sun and moon will be joined together (by going one into the other or folded up or deprived of their light).{1}",footnotes:1:[{75:9} Narrated Abu Hurairah رضي الله عنه : The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, "The sun and the moon will be folded up (or joined together or deprived of their lights) on the Day of Resurrection." (See the Qur’ân Verse 75:9) (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.4, Hadith No.422).]
  76,1,"Has there not been over man a period of time, when he was not a thing worth mentioning?"
  76,2,"Verily, We have created man from Nutfah (drops) of mixed semen (sexual discharge of man and woman), in order to try him: so We made him hearer and seer."
  76,3,"Verily, We showed him the way, whether he be grateful or ungrateful."